\begin_layout Subsection*
2 Examples of recent research projects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Study for masterplan
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is possible to apply directly syntax to help design ; this example of
 project shows how a proposal of masterplan is done and how the designer
 can move pieces of it to see the consequences through the self-organisation
 of the rest of the plan.
 The modification can be done at different scales, from furnitures sometimes
 to the overall floor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The techniques used are 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

agent-based aggregation
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, what seems to be a computational design of possible configuration (not
 more precisions since it appears to be confidential for the company).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The figure [] shows the final result for the Hong Kong polytechnic University,
 after the created masterplan has been integrated to the other sections.
\end_layout

